{
  "texts": [
    "For this, ChatGPT was trained with a massive dataset sourced from the internet.",
    "This dataset includes a wide range of text genres, such as news, articles, scientific papers, social media posts, etc.",
    "in different topics and languages [8].",
    "The exact size and composition of the training dataset can be estimated to be on the order of hundreds of gigabytes or more [9].",
    "The goal of the training process is to learn patterns and relationships within the text data that allow the model to generate human-like responses to various questions and prompts [10].Several existing LLMs include BERT [11], Transformer-XL [12], Megatron [13], Jurassic-1 [14], ELECTRA (Efficiently Learning an Encoder that Classifies Token Replacements Accurately) [15], Gopher [16], etc."
  ]
}